Well I guess you can’t hold on to something once you let it go 
But I know a place 
Where we can be us
I know it ain’t real 
But it’s real enough 
From sun going down to sun coming up 
It’s like you’re here with me 
Whenever I close my eyes
It’s taking me back in time
Been drowning in dreams lately 
Like it’s 2019 baby 
Whenever I’m missing you 
Call you up but I can’t get through
Don’t know where you sleep lately 
But I’ll see you in my dreams maybe 
We can catch up, drive down our old street
If all that we were is all that we’ll ever be
It’s bittersweet
At least a girl can dream 
I guess that I’m taking what I can get 
‘Cause I don’t get nothing new from your friends 
If you got the harder side of the break 
Then why is it harder for me to take 
There’s so much I might never get to say, ay
But I know a place 
Where we can be us

But it’s real enough

It’s like you’re here with me 
Whenever I close my eyes
It’s taking me back in time
Been drowning in dreams lately 
Like it’s 2019 baby 
Whenever I’m missing you 
Call you up but I can’t get through
Don’t know where you sleep lately 
But I’ll see you in my dreams maybe 
We can catch up, drive down our old street
If all that we were is all that we’ll ever be
It’s bittersweet
At least a girl can dream 
I-I-I know it’s only in my mind
Playing three nights on the stereo
Like a movie scene, DiCaprio 
Oh l-I-I put my make up on just to fall asleep
It’s like you’re here with me 
Whenever I close my eyes
It’s taking me back in time
Been drowning in dreams lately 
Like it’s 2019 baby 
Whenever I’m missing you 
Call you up but I can’t get through
Don’t know where you sleep lately 
But I’ll see you in my dreams maybe 
We can catch up, drive down our old street
If all that we were is something we’ll never be
It’s bittersweet
Can we be friends at least

A love that I could not forsake

Well, in the moment
You weren’t all that kind
You with your wide-eyed grin’s all I can see
When I think of that time

Promises spoken
All coming back as lies
But you with your soft, sweet kiss is all I miss
In the back of my mind

Did me wrong in the past
And I know it was bad
But you burn inside my memory so well
You caramel
You’re caramel

Your cigarette breath
Thick on your open mouth
Maple and amber clouds and coﬀee grounds

Oh

It was what we deserved

Yeah, you burn inside my memory so well
You caramel
You’re caramel

And the longer burn, the sweeter that you smell
You caramel
You’re caramel

Sweet taste in my mouth
I can’t get it out
I want you back now
And we’re making out
Drunk, sleeping on my couch
Now when I hear you’re in town
I just want caramel
Ooh
I heard you’re in town
I want you back now
Come over to my house
There’s space on my couch

Yeah, you burn inside my memory so well
You caramel
You’re caramel

snippet.title: Le-one - YAMAL (Testo/Lyrics)
snippet.description:
♫ Le-one - YAMAL (Testo/Lyrics)
⭐ Stream: 

🎤 Testo/Lyrics: Le-one - YAMAL 

[Intro]
(Me scrive Tracy, Melany fa 'o pressing)
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah
(Ale è juta 'a fore pecché m'ha visto cu Mary)
(Ce fumammo 'a Mary, moltiplicammo 'e zere)
(Scengo c''o 300 'int'ô quartiere 'nzieme ê devil, ê devil)

[Strofa 1]
Nn'hê capito, chesta me sta massaggianno
Mentre chella messaggianno
Che talento a sidic'anne, me paro Lamine Yamal
C'avesse na medaglia d'oro comme 'sti cullanе
Guarda ccà comme me stanno cinche K appisе 'nganna
'A-'A porto 'int'ô Tarì c''o Ferrari
A-Accussí accatte 'e diamante
Però basta ca t'è chiaro ca i' e te 'nzieme nun stammo

[Pre-Ritornello 1]
Ammò, nun tengo capa 'e stà sulo 'nzieme a te
Bella 'a cumpagna toja, jà, faccimmo 'e cose a tre

[Ritornello]
Me scrive Tracy, Melany fa 'o pressing
Ale è juta 'a fore pecché m'ha visto cu Mary
Ce fumammo 'a Mary, moltiplicammo 'e zere
Scengo c''o 300 'int'ô quartiere 'nzieme ê devil, ê devil (Ê devil, ê devil)


[Strofa 2]
Chi-Chi-Chiste stanno parlanno, m''e driblo comme Neymar
Contro tengo a tutte quante, ma me sento Diego Armando
Mettenno nu Rolex a destra e uno a sinistra (Okay)
Tutt''e cose, fra', l'hê viste sulamente dint'ê film
Uh Madonna, comme è bella 'sta guagliona (Okay)
Ma è cchiù bello 'stu Daytona (Okay)
Cu quadrante tutto d'oro, cchiù ggiallo d''e facce loro (Oh-oh)

[Pre-Ritornello 2]
Statte accorto, te sorpasso, vide 'a morte 'nfaccia (Okay)
E vide 'e fà 'o bravo, staje avenno a che fà ch''e pazze (Okay, oka')

[Ritornello]
Me-Me-Me scrive Tracy, Melany fa 'o pressing
Ale è juta 'a fore pecché m'ha visto cu Mary
Ce fumammo 'a Mary, moltiplicammo 'e zere
Scengo c''o 300 'int'ô quartiere 'nzieme ê devil, ê devil
[Outro]
Ê devil, ê devil, ê devil, 'int'ô quartiere
Ê devil, ê devil, ê devil, scengo 'int'ô quartiere
Ê devil, ê devil, ê devil, ê devil
Melany fa 'o pressing
